      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p><a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661413/Aggregate+Volumes\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661413\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Aggregate Volumes</a> can decrease the render time for volumes by combining them into a single structure for the renderer to process.  To get started with aggregate volumes in RfH, there are two steps: setting the aggregate name on the volume geometries and specifying a matching aggregate name in the integrator.</p><h3 id=\"AggregateVolumes-StepOne:Groupvolumesintoaggregates\">Step One: Group volumes into aggregates</h3><p>First, select the OBJ nodes containing the volumes you want to be grouped in an aggregate. You can then use the &quot;Aggregate&quot; shelf tool on the RenderMan shelf, the &quot;aggregate Volume&quot; menu tool in the RenderMan menu, or you can manually add the ri_volume_aggregate rendering parameter to the OBJ. </p><p>If you use either of the aggregate tools, you will get a popup asking you to specify the name of the aggregate. By default this is globalVolumeAggregate. When you accept, the tool will add ri_volume_aggregate and ri_volume_dsominmax to your obj with the given aggregate name. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"591\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-25-51.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122614&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=205\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-25-51.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122614&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"236\" data-width=\"678\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644056\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2021-11-2_10-25-51.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644033\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"680e77b1-9941-440e-971d-7dcb7e4d9c20\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-25-51.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122614&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=678&amp;height=236 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-25-51.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122614&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=205 1x\"></span><p>You may instead want to specify volume aggregates on the Geometry level. To do this, you will need to add a primitive attribute called ri_volume_aggregate. If ri_volume_aggregate is set as both an object parameter and a geometry attribute, the geometry attribute value will be used.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"591\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-36-55.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=381\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-36-55.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"392\" data-width=\"608\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644047\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2021-11-2_10-36-55.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644033\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"60dbd145-7f55-4223-a5b7-1d8ad8b41041\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-36-55.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=608&amp;height=392 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-36-55.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=381 1x\"></span><p>There are no custom tools for setting up volume aggregates in Solaris. You must add the setting with the Geometry Render Setting LOP. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"591\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-31-40.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=390\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-31-40.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"435\" data-width=\"659\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644053\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2021-11-2_10-31-40.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644033\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"c91c6ae4-096b-4733-baab-41c4b04938f8\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-31-40.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=659&amp;height=435 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-31-40.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=390 1x\"></span><h3 id=\"AggregateVolumes-StepTwo:Specifyvolumeaggregatenameintheintegrator\">Step Two: Specify volume aggregate name in the integrator</h3><p>PxrPathTracer has four parameters related to aggregate volumes.  In the simple case, you'll only need to set the global &quot;Volume Aggregate&quot; parameter.  But since the standard visibility attributes don't work within a volume aggregate, you may run into cases where you need to specify separate aggregate names for each type of visibility (camera, indirect, and transmission).  These can be specified in the other three override parameters.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"a3e2298a-abd4-464f-a54c-5882a6112c4b\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>If a volume aggregate name has not been specified to the integrator, any volumes that are part of a volume aggregate will not render</p></div></div><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"591\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-33-18.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=381\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-33-18.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"424\" data-width=\"656\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644050\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2021-11-2_10-33-18.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644033\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"414c0993-9432-4ce9-b6a0-e54241acd71d\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-33-18.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=656&amp;height=424 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644033/image2021-11-2_10-33-18.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433122377&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=591&amp;height=381 1x\"></span>"
    }
